# Controller Input Migration from Vivsi1/Winlator Bionic

## Phase 1: Setup & Research
- [x] Reclone WinNative repo
- [/] Download Vivsi1 APK and source zip
- [ ] Decompile APK if needed for missing files
- [ ] Review Vivsi1 bionic controller/input files thoroughly
- [ ] Review WinNative current controller/input files
- [ ] Map all controller-related files and dependencies

## Phase 2: Planning
- [ ] Create comprehensive implementation plan
- [ ] Identify all files to add/modify/replace
- [ ] Identify imagefs/system file requirements
- [ ] Get user approval on plan

## Phase 3: Implementation
- [ ] Replace/update input bridge files
- [ ] Replace/update controller driver/kernel files
- [ ] Replace/update fake device / evshim files
- [ ] Update native C/JNI code as needed
- [ ] Update imagefs system files if needed
- [ ] Preserve existing UI (no UI changes)

## Phase 4: Verification
- [ ] Compare every file against Vivsi1 source
- [ ] Verify no missing dependencies
- [ ] Build with assembleDebug
- [ ] Create walkthrough
